Description: Body sherd of East Greek, possibly Aeolian, grey ware large pottery vessel, possibly a krater or dinos; exterior: worn dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The fabric finds parallels with British Museum 1888,0601.637 which was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen (Bonn). The results placed the fabric (sample NAUK 64) in NAA group G and the origin was determined to be Aeolis.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.019)
